channel.title: /\/\/\ need professional help for my compiler /\/\/\
channel.description:
Ok, loads of people call me a noob for not knowing how to fix this error.. but they're wrong, I'm not a noob ..
I have Mod Taharocks or who ever's compiler, I've successfully installed JDK 6.2.
I know I have because Java.com verified it. It's still saying 'You need Java 5.0 or 6.0.'
I don't want any flaming like I do all of the time. Don't say 'you need to set variables' I've already done so..
I've got latest version of JDK. So what now? :confused:
